Reasoning: The paper deals with algorithms for constructing canonical intersection models for circular-arc graphs and hypergraphs, as well as solving the Star System Problem for these classes of graphs. This involves topics such as graph theory, computational geometry, and complexity theory, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
